            <fr:title text="Jordan block">Jordan block</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> be a unital <fr:link href="/ring-0001/" title="Ring" uri="http://localhost:8000/ring-0001/" display-uri="ring-0001" type="local">Ring</fr:link>, let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda \in  R]]></fr:tex>, let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n\in \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> be a positive integer. A <html:dfn>Jordan Block</html:dfn> of size <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> with eigenvalue <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda ]]></fr:tex> is an <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n\times  n]]></fr:tex> matrix which looks like
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\begin {pmatrix}
\lambda  &      1  &        &         &   \\
        & \lambda  & \ddots  &         &   \\
        &         & \ddots  &  1      &   \\
        &         &        & \lambda  & 1 \\
        &         &        &         & \lambda \end {pmatrix}.]]></fr:tex>
That is to say, the upper subdiagonal are all 1, the diagonal entries are all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda ]]></fr:tex>, and all other entries are zero.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>20</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>remark</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>This is also called an <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n\times  n]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn>elementary Jordan matrix</html:dfn> with eigenvalue <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda ]]></fr:tex>, among other various similar terms.</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
